2 Preprocessing

2.1 load data

merge of:

  • output hovernet
  • purity computed with different methods from paper nature
  • slide.tsv metadata from TCGA

2.2 new variables

tcgaOV$tcga_purity_mean <- rowMeans(tcgaOV[, c("ESTIMATE", "ABSOLUTE", "LUMP", "IHC", "CPE")], na.rm = TRUE)
tcgaOV$purity_hovernet <- as.numeric(tcgaOV$neoplastic)/as.numeric(tcgaOV$num_nuclei)
tcgaOV$inflam_perc <- as.numeric(tcgaOV$inflammatory)/as.numeric(tcgaOV$num_nuclei)
tcgaOV$strom_perc <- as.numeric(tcgaOV$stromal)/as.numeric(tcgaOV$num_nuclei)
tcgaOV$benign_perc <- as.numeric(tcgaOV$benign_epithelial)/as.numeric(tcgaOV$num_nuclei)
tcgaOV$necrot_perc <- as.numeric(tcgaOV$necrotic)/as.numeric(tcgaOV$num_nuclei)

4.1 PCA plot

ggplot(pca_df, aes(x = PC1, y = PC2, color = inflammatory)) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +
  labs(title = "PCA - inflammatory", x = "PC1", y = "PC2", color = "Inflammation") +
  scale_color_viridis(option = "D") +
  theme_minimal()

9 Clustering

9.1 Hierarchical Clustering

## clusters_hc
##  1  2  3 
## 46 16 45

tcgaOV_tab$clusters_hc <- clusters_hc
tcgaOV_tab2 <- tcgaOV_tab[,-c(40)]
tcgaOV_tab2 %>%
  tbl_summary(
    by = "clusters_hc",                                               # stratify entire table by outcome
    statistic = list(all_continuous() ~ "{median} ({p25}, {p75})",        # stats and format for continuous columns
                     all_categorical() ~ "{n} / {N} ({p}%)"),   # stats and format for categorical columns
    digits = all_continuous() ~ 1,                              # rounding for continuous columns
    type   = all_categorical() ~ "categorical",                 # force all categorical levels to display
    # label  = list(                                              # display labels for column names
    #   outcome   ~ "Outcome",
    #   age_years ~ "Age (years)",
    #   gender    ~ "Gender",
    #   temp      ~ "Temperature",
    #   hospital  ~ "Hospital"),
    missing_text = "Missing"                                    # how missing values should display
  ) %>%
  add_p(pvalue_fun = ~style_pvalue(.x, digits = 2)) %>%   # comparing values by "both" column
  add_overall()
